headline: From software to real estate, U.S. sectors under the grip of AI scare trade
summary: Wall Street is in the grip of disruption worries from AI. It first started with investors dumping shares of software companies but soon spread to sectors seen as vulnerable to automation, driving sharp losses in U.S. stocks this week. The AI scare trade did not spare even sectors ‌such as private credit, real estate brokers, data analytics, legal services and insurers.

headline: JPMorgan Flags 'AI-Resilient' Software Names After Selloff
summary: JPMorgan believes AI won't disrupt software companies as much as feared. They recommend investing in quality names.

headline: 1 Nasdaq 100 Stock on Our Watchlist and 2 Facing Headwinds
summary: The Nasdaq 100 (^NDX) is home to some of the biggest success stories in tech and growth investing. However, certain stocks in the index face challenges like profitability concerns, rising costs, or shifts in market trends.
